The White House Conference on Aging, hosted by President Obama, focuses on the issues facing Americans as they plan for retirement, care for older loved ones, and work to improve our quality of life as we age. The President announced new steps to ensure that Americans have the tools they need to prepare for retirement. The conference also highlighted the importance of programs such as Medicare, Medicaid, and Social Security, and the role of technology in the lives of older Americans. The conference also announced various actions and initiatives from the private sector to support older Americans, such as developing technology-driven tools, providing free home care, and improving access to transportation options. Additionally, the conference addressed topics such as workplace retirement savings, long-term care, healthy aging, elder justice, and preventing elder abuse.